2026 RR 3504/DI JR

Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring Brad Eisenhart upon
2 his retirement.
3 Whereas, After more than three decades of dedicated
4 service, Brad Eisenhart, the Great Lakes Area Director of
5 Disposal Operations for Waste Management (WM), is
6 embarking on a well-deserved retirement;
7 Whereas, Brad started at WM in May 1992 as an
8 Engineering Intern at Suburban Landfill in Ohio, and by
9 October of that year, he had accepted a Site Engineer position
10 in Indiana;
11 Whereas, Brad's career progression at WM is a testament
12 to his passion for learning and growth as evidenced by his
13 trajectory through increasingly impactful roles, including
14 District Manager at Twin Bridges Landfill and ultimately
15 Director of Disposal Operations for Ohio and Indiana;
16 Whereas, A highlight of Brad's career was leading the
17 development of the $27 million Crossroads Rail Facility, where
18 he managed the design, construction, and site operations of this
19 pivotal project that positioned WM as an industry leader in
2026 RR 3504/DI JR

2
1 innovative waste management solutions;
2 Whereas, In addition to his operational expertise, Brad's
3 commitment to environmental stewardship has shone through
4 his developing of the Indiana Master Naturalist Program at
5 Twin Bridges to foster ecological awareness and education;
6 Whereas, Outside of his work, Brad is devoted to
7 community services, having served on the Board of Directors
8 for the Greater Danville Chamber of Commerce, the Parks
9 Foundation of Hendricks County, the Hendricks County Parks
10 & Recreation Board, and the Danville Optimist Youth Soccer
11 League; and
12 Whereas, Brad also volunteers with the Hendricks County
13 Solid Waste District Citizens Advisory Committee, Boy Scout
14 Troop 302, Twin Bridges Skeet & Trap Club, and the Danville
15 Optimist Club: Therefore,
16 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
17 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
18 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors Brad Eisenhart
19 upon his retirement and thanks him for his years of community
20 service.
21 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is directed to
22 transmit copies of this Resolution to Brad Eisenhart.
